This is makeup pseudocode made for the custom analyzer.                                   |
In this case, it will be detailing the processToken function in this particular analyzer  |
											                                              |
==========================================================================================/
(It might be useful to find a way to make it account for capitalization if the character can be capitalized, but that's neither here nor there.)
MAGIC LETTER (A Constant single-character string, like "b" or "m")
LETTER OCCURANCES (a counter for occurances of the MAGIC LETTER)
GENERAL OCCURANCES (a counter for every character)

processToken(TOKEN(a single word)) {
	Iterate through TOKEN
	At each character in TOKEN:
		if it's equal to the MAGIC LETTER, add 1 to LETTER OCCURANCES and GENERAL OCCURANCES
		if it isn't add 1 to GENERAL OCCURANCES
}
after this, we can do math with the counters, like dividing GENERAL OCCURANCES by LETTER OCCURANCES to get a percentage use of the MAGIC LETTER
These will be used in the output file




